```python
from Crypto.Util.number import bytes_to_long, long_to_bytes
from math import gcd 
import json
f = open('mods' , 'r').read()
e = 65537
mods = json.loads(f)
f = open('cipher' , 'r').read()
ciphers = json.loads(f)
l = []
n1 =0
n2=0
for i in mods :
	for j in mods: 
		if gcd(i , j ) !=1 and i != j :
			n1 = i 
			n2 = j 
	if n1 > 0 :
		break 
	 


#
#


print(gcd(n1,n2))
p = gcd(n1,n2)
q = max(n1 , n2 ) // p 
phi = (p-1)*(q-1)
d = pow(e,-1 , phi)
m = pow(ciphers[mods.index(max(n1,n2))] , d , max(n1, n2 ))
print(long_to_bytes(m))

```
